body: the hlt is a converted turkey frier the mash water is heated to 172 degrees and then run through the lines and wort chiller via pump and circulated back into the hlt for extra sanitation obviously there is no need to hook up the wort chiller when heating your mash water but i like to have everything set up at the beginning of the brew after about 5 minutes of circulating the water through the lines i kill the pump place the hose into my pre heated mash tun igloo cooler with gallon markings start the pump again fill the tun to the desired volume and cap it when the water is at strike temp 168 2 degrees i mash in i called it simple in the title but after typing all of this i am beginning to think it a bit more complicated than i originally presumed

name: adkryan
body: it was a hot saturday in south florida longboarding with my buddy jak we walked 6 flights of stairs to cruise down a vacant parking garage and did this several times graffiti in the stairwell the smell of american spirits burning and beef tongue tacos in our bellies it was one of the simplest most awesome days of my life we drove to the beach to check the swells and then headed back to his place so i could get my car and jet i was driving for about 3 minutes before i realized that i left my board in the back of his vehicle i almost turned around and then i said screw it it ll give me an excuse to hang with him again next weekend or something do it all over again it ll be awesome every day since that day i wished i had turned around because that was the last time i ever saw jak one night that week he decided to drive across alligator alley to meet a girl in ft meyers as soon as he hit the alley his tire blew out and his vehicle flipped he was alive when the paramedic arrived but died in the ambulance en route to the hospital his dog layla was in the car with him but sustained no major injuries as for my board it was in the back of the vehicle during the crash after a couple of weeks passed i contacted his relatives to try and locate my board it had ended up all the way in massachusetts at his relative s house after telling them my story they immediately mailed it back to me it arrived last night this is a picture of it in my driveway last night after taking it out of the box i teared up when i noticed bits of dog hair on the deck i couldn t bring myself to take a ride last night just too emotional i leave this here for you now because in a way you the longboarding community are my spiritual outlet to jak so thanks for that i m going for that ride now edit here http imgur com a r1scp 0 are a few pics of jak
